cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text classification for detecting vandalism in Wikidata. It also involves machine learning techniques for online learning and prediction. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the detection of malicious edits in a large database of structured information. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) as it deals with the detection of vandalism in a database of structured information. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for online learning and prediction. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the detection of malicious edits in a database, which is a security concern.
